1. Purpose

This document defines a possible direction for Phase 3 Wave 2 in TraceFold.

It exists to answer:

why a bot/adapters wave is a reasonable next step after Phase 3 Wave 1
what problem this wave is actually trying to solve
what TG bot / Feishu bot should mean inside TraceFold
what boundaries must remain frozen
what work packages should structure the wave
what should explicitly remain out of scope

This document is a direction note only.
It does not yet authorize broad execution or implementation prompts.

2. Current Project Position

TraceFold remains:

a local-first personal data workbench / personal data platform
centered on the main chain
Capture -> Parse -> Pending -> Confirm -> Formal Record -> Query / Analysis / Derivation
centered on the application service layer as the only business-logic center
centered on SQLite as the single source of truth
centered on Web as the main business interface
with Desktop as shell-level entry
with Telegram as lightweight adapter

Phase 3 Wave 1 has already produced bounded closures around:

Input-side daily-use improvement
Quick Capture
Bulk Intake with Preview
Capture Inbox / Intake Triage
Readback/detail usability improvement
detail hierarchy tightening
density/readback polish
bounded Workbench readback-support polish

This means the system already has a stronger Web intake and readback surface than before.

The next reasonable problem is no longer only “make the Web better.”
The next reasonable problem is:

make it easier to begin recording from the places where users naturally start typing.

3. Why Wave 2 Exists

The motivation for this wave is simple:

daily use improves only partially if input is still mostly tied to opening the Web workbench first
for many real-life use cases, the natural starting point for recording is a chat-like surface
the user explicitly wants recording to feel more like “drop a message in quickly”
this is especially relevant for:
Telegram
Feishu

So the problem is not “how to create new product lines,” but:

how to reduce the friction of starting a record by using lightweight message-based adapters that still feed the same unified chain.

Wave 2 therefore should not be interpreted as “bot productization.”

It should be interpreted as:

lightweight capture adapters for lower-friction entry into the existing system.

